

get_Rx_cserrno(3N)                             get_Rx_cserrno(3N)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] file -lnsl #include <rx.h> #include <cs.h>

       int get_Rx_cserrno(void);

       int set_Rx_cserrno(int value);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  functions  get_Rx_cserrno and set_Rx_cserrno retrieve
       and set the value of  Rx_cserrno  in  multi-threaded  pro-
       grams.  These functions are needed in multi-threaded envi-
       ronments  because  each  thread  keeps  its  own  copy  of
       Rx_cserrno.

       After  a  failed  call  to  rexecve, if Rx_errno is set to
       RXE_CONNPROB, then the value of Rx_cserrno  indicates  the
       specific connection server problem.

UUssaaggee
       While  get_Rx_cserrno  and set_Rx_cserrno are designed for
       use in multi-threaded applications, they are available for
       use  in  non-reentrant  code, and may be incorporated if a
       need is anticipated to convert  to  reentrant  code  at  a
       later date.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       get_Rx_cserrno  returns  the value of Rx_cserrno, or -1 in
       case of error.

       set_Rx_cserrno sets Rx_cserrno to value, and returns 0 for
       success and -1 for failure.

